  "debates": [
    {
      "id": "d1",
      "positions": [
        "Nylon wins on strength/working force and is the conventional choice; its wet penalty is a manageable, reversible plasticization effect.",
        "Nylon's water absorption and wet-stretch are disqualifying for all-weather use because absorbed water plasticizes it, collapsing modulus and dimensional stability and driving the bagging-out failure.",
        "PET/polyolefin (PET, HDPE, polypropylene, UHMWPE) trade some dry feel for near-zero water uptake and dimensional stability, the better all-weather baseline."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "d2",
      "positions": [
        "Coatings deliver strong water and UV protection and add useful body/abrasion resistance to existing nylon mesh.",
        "Finishes carry stiffness/weight/hold and durability costs and wear off, so an intrinsically hydrophobic, stable yarn is preferable.",
        "Coatings and stabilizers delay but do not eliminate degradation, and their combined behavior on fine pigmented mesh is unverified."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "d3",
      "positions": [
        "Knotless construction reduces projected area/drag and removes the knot strength-loss site, favoring a cleaner, lighter, stronger mesh.",
        "Knots and knotted geometry are the controllable levers that set diamond solidity and pocket shape, and nylon knotted mono can have the best knot-fatigue durability."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "d4",
      "positions": [
        "Monofilament minimizes water-trapping surface and is the basis of the best-characterized knot/strength behavior, and larger-diameter mono gives higher breaking load.",
        "Multifilament yarns and high-performance polyethylene filament give superior tensile-fatigue and abrasion behavior, relevant to long service life."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "d5",
      "positions": [
        "UHMWPE/HPPE is the strongest, lightest, most abrasion- and fatigue-resistant netting fiber and can be UV-hardened by blending.",
        "UHMWPE takes large permanent set under load and degrades fastest under UV unprotected, so its dimensional behavior threatens wet/loaded pocket-legality."
      ]
    }
  ],
